I have noticed that you guys stick with radius arms instead of putting on a 3 or 4 link front suspension. Is there a reason for this such as rules that don't allow modification of suspension mounting points? A 3 or 4 link would allow for much better articulation and could even improve on road and high speed handling characteristics.

snippet.textDisplay:
You boys have conquered Australia. No question about that. Ya'll know your wheeling on the world's stage. Is it time to have an American tour? Here are 10 in one state that will challenge or make Commando Trail look easy. All are in the state of Colorado with some real mountains. Want snow? We have it in spades? All. Year. Long. Give a shout when you get here. There are 49 other states that have a beaten path to play on. Americans love ya'll. We are wishing we could get some of the gear and rigs you blokes run. Bring us a show and pack a bunch of parts to share. Holler when you get here. I'll show Shauno how to cook a proper meal.
10 - Blanca Peak
9 - Iron Chest
8 - Minesweeper
7 - Billings Canyon
6 - 21 Road
5 - Die Trying
4 - Carnage BV
3 - Calamity Canyon
2 - Cactus Ridge
1 (most difficult)- Independence/Patriot
